    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missed scheduling opportunities due to unprocessed SR in PUCCH format 2/3/4 UCI indications\n\n### Summary\nNR gNB scheduler was missing scheduling opportunities for UEs that sent Scheduling Requests (SR) on PUCCH format 2/3/4. The root cause was that the `unpack_nr_uci_pucch_2_3_4` function correctly unpacked the SR payload but did not extract the SR indication bit, making it inaccessible to the scheduler.\n\nUnlike PUCCH format 0/1 which has a dedicated `sr_indication` field, format 2/3/4 only stored the raw SR payload. The MAC scheduler had a TODO comment indicating SR was not being handled, causing UEs requesting uplink resources via SR on format 2/3/4 to be ignored.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder load testing with mixed PUCCH formats, UEs using PUCCH format 2/3/4 with active SR were consistently not scheduled for uplink transmission, while identical UEs using PUCCH format 0/1 were scheduled correctly. This led to increased access delays and reduced throughput for affected UEs.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable in scenarios with high UE density where format 2/3/4 is preferred due to better multiplexing capabilities.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/public_inc/nfapi_nr_interface_scf.h`: Added `sr_indication` field to `nfapi_nr_sr_pdu_2_3_4_t` structure for consistency with format 0/1\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7.c`: Modified `unpack_nr_uci_pucch_2_3_4` to extract SR indication from payload[0] bit 0\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Updated `copy_uci_indication_sr_pdu_2_3_4` to copy new field\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_uci.c`: Replaced TODO with SR processing logic using new field\n- `nfapi/tests/p7/nr_fapi_uci_indication_test.c`: Updated test function to populate new field\n\n"
}